The paper focuses on designing artificial intelligence for games using deep reinforcement learning and evolutionary algorithms. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses multi-objective optimization, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Game theory (cs.GT) is also mentioned in the abstract. The paper also mentions the use of style-oriented learning, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) depending on the specific implementation.
